<?xml version="1.0"?><xliff version="1.2" xmlns="urn:oasis:names:tc:xliff:document:1.2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:xliff:document:1.2 xliff-core-1.2-transitional.xsd"><file datatype="xml" original="4-exercise-add-intents-and-entities.md" source-language="en-US" target-language="en-US"><header><tool tool-id="mdxliff" tool-name="mdxliff" tool-version="1.0-1931010" tool-company="Microsoft" /><xliffext:skl_file_name xmlns:xliffext="urn:microsoft:content:schema:xliffextensions">4-exercise-add-intents-and-entities.4a5463e618b86c2f751a238b0be497fcba9cc102.skl</xliffext:skl_file_name><xliffext:version xmlns:xliffext="urn:microsoft:content:schema:xliffextensions">1.2</xliffext:version><xliffext:ms.openlocfilehash xmlns:xliffext="urn:microsoft:content:schema:xliffextensions">478d761faa5d403c47ac8f9448639a7f572aeaee</xliffext:ms.openlocfilehash><xliffext:ms.lasthandoff xmlns:xliffext="urn:microsoft:content:schema:xliffextensions">04/24/2019</xliffext:ms.lasthandoff><xliffext:ms.openlocfilepath xmlns:xliffext="urn:microsoft:content:schema:xliffextensions">learn-pr\data-ai-cert\create-and-publish-a-LUIS-model\includes\4-exercise-add-intents-and-entities.md</xliffext:ms.openlocfilepath></header><body><group id="content" extype="content"><trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Our next step for the PictureBotLUIS app is creating intents that map to user requests.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>We want our picture-management bot to understand how to:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Find pictures.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Share pictures on social media.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Order prints of pictures.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Greet the user.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Let’s create intents for each of these items.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>There is one intent already present named <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>None<ept id="p1">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Random utterances that don’t map to any of your intents can be mapped to this intent.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>+ Create new intent<ept id="p1">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Name the first intent <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Greeting<ept id="p1">**</ept>, and then select <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Done<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Because our scenario for this application is to integrate with a bot, you'll provide examples of utterances that users might say when greeting the bot initially.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Enter a greeting utterance, such as <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>hello<ept id="p1">**</ept>, and press Enter.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Repeat the previous step to create values for each of the following utterances: <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>hi<ept id="p1">**</ept>, <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>hola<ept id="p2">**</ept>, <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>yo<ept id="p3">**</ept>, <bpt id="p4">**</bpt>hey<ept id="p4">**</ept>, <bpt id="p5">**</bpt>greetings<ept id="p5">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You should always provide at least five example utterances for each intent.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Your utterances for the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Greeting<ept id="p1">**</ept> intent should look similar to the following image:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Utterances for the Greeting intent</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create another intent named <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>SearchPics<ept id="p1">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add the following values as utterances for the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>SearchPics<ept id="p1">**</ept> intent:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>find outdoor pics<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>are there pictures of a train?<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="122" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>find pictures of food<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="123" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>search for photos of boys playing<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="124" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>give me colorful pictures<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="125" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>show me beach pics<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="126" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>I want to find dog photos<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="127" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>find pictures of german shepherds<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="128" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>search for pictures of men indoors<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="129" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>show me pictures of men wearing glasses<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="130" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>I want to see pics of smiling people<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="131" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>show me baby pics<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="132" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Create entities</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="133" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Next, let's create the entities we need to capture specific requests from users.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="134" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, when users want to search the pictures, they might specify what they're looking for.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="135" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the left column, select <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Entities<ept id="p1">**</ept>, and then select <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Create new entity<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="136" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Name the entity <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>facet<ept id="p1">**</ept> (to represent one way to identify an image).</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="137" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Select <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Simple<ept id="p1">**</ept> for <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Entity type<ept id="p2">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="138" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Then select <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Done<ept id="p1">**</ept>.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="139" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Adding an entity named facet, of type Simple</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="140" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Map search subjects to the facet entity</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="141" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Next, we have to teach LUIS how to pick out the search subject as the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>facet<ept id="p1">**</ept> entity.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="142" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Whatever the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>facet<ept id="p1">**</ept> entity picks up is what the app will search for.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="143" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Switch back to the Intents and select the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>SearchPics<ept id="p1">**</ept> intent.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="144" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Hover over the utterance and click the keyword that specifies the <bpt id="p1">_</bpt>search subject<ept id="p1">_</ept>, and then select the <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>facet<ept id="p2">**</ept> entity.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="145" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>For example, if the utterance is "show me baby pics", the subject would be "baby".</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="146" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Screenshot showing utterance selection to tie it to an entity</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="147" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Using multiword keywords, such as "german shepherds", is a bit tricky.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="148" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click the first word in the keyword, move the cursor to the second word, and then click again.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="149" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Then move the cursor into the entity selection pop-up list.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="150" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Be sure not to move the cursor outside the borders, or you'll lose the selection.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="151" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Your progress should look similar to the following image:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="152" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Keywords selected as facet entities, shown by the term "facet" selected in the image</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="153" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Add two more intents with related utterances, as shown in the following table:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="154" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Intent name</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="155" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Utterances</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="156" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>SharePic<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="157" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Share this pic<ept id="p1">**</ept>, <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>Can you tweet that?<ept id="p2">**</ept>, <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>Post to Twitter<ept id="p3">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="158" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>OrderPic<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="159" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Print this picture<ept id="p1">**</ept>, <bpt id="p2">**</bpt>I would like to order prints<ept id="p2">**</ept>, <bpt id="p3">**</bpt>Can I get an 8x10 of that one?<ept id="p3">**</ept>, <bpt id="p4">**</bpt>Order wallets<ept id="p4">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="160" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To finish out the exercise, add some utterances to the existing <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>None<ept id="p1">**</ept> intent.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="161" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Make sure these utterances don't match the context of this LUIS app.</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="162" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Some examples are:</source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="163" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>I'm hungry for pizza<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="164" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Search videos<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit><trans-unit id="165" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><bpt id="p1">**</bpt>Show me how to drive a car<ept id="p1">**</ept></source>
        </trans-unit></group></body></file></xliff>